- content_for :title, 'Access Overview'
.d-flex
  %h1= content_for :title
= render 'menus/admin_tabs'
.access-overview
  .row
    .col-sm
      .well
        %h3 Building and Using Access Controls
        %p
          %strong Access Controls
          are used to grant users access to data and control the permissions those users have when accessing the granted data.  Access is goverend by the intersection of permissions from the role, users from the associated user group, and information from the collection.

        %p.access-description
          Each
          %span.access-control.color-tag<
            = link_to 'access control', '#', tabindex: '0', data: {container: '.access-overview', toggle: :popover, placement: :top, html: true, trigger: :focus, content: "<p>Accss Controls are used to grant users access to data and permissions.  Each access control consists of one Role, one User Group, and one Collection. Access is governed by the intersection of permission from the role, entities from the collection, and users from the user group.</p><p>#{link_to 'Manage Access Controls', admin_access_controls_path}</p>", title: 'Access Control'}
          consists of one
          %span.permission-role.color-tag<
            = link_to 'permission role', '#', tabindex: '1', data: {container: '.access-overview', toggle: :popover, placement: :top, html: true, trigger: :focus, content: "<p>User groups are used to logically group users who need similar access.  User groups are combined with roles and collections via access controls.  The intersection of role, collection, and user group determines what each person can do and see within the warehouse.</p><p>#{link_to 'Manage Roles', admin_roles_path}</p>", title: 'Permission Role'}
          %span.user-group.color-tag<
            = link_to 'user group', '#', tabindex: '1', data: {container: '.access-overview', toggle: :popover, placement: :top, html: true, trigger: :focus, content: "<p>User groups are used to logically group users who need similar access.  User groups are combined with roles and collections via access controls.  The interesction of role, collection, and user group, determins what each person can do and see within the warehouse.</p><p>#{link_to 'Manage User Groups', admin_user_groups_path}</p>", title: 'User Group'}
          and
          %span.collection.color-tag<
            = link_to 'collection', '#', tabindex: '1', data: {container: '.access-overview', toggle: :popover, placement: :top, html: true, trigger: :focus, content: "<p>Collections are used to assign access to particular sets of data.  Users inherit data access from the collection. groups are combined with roles and collections via access controls.  The interesction of role, collection, and user group, determins what each person can do and see within the warehouse.</p><p>#{link_to 'Manage Collections', admin_collections_path}</p>", title: 'Collection'}
            \.
    .col-sm
      .well
        %h3 Common Things Users Do
        %ul.list-unstyled
          %li= link_to 'Manage User Roles and Permissions', admin_roles_path
          %li= link_to 'Manage Users', admin_users_path
          %li= link_to 'Create Collections', admin_collections_path
          %li= link_to 'Grant Access to a Report', admin_access_controls_path
          %li= link_to 'Grant Access to Additional Projects', admin_access_controls_path
